tellegen
Copyright 2026 Samuel Talkington and contributors

tellegen is a differentiable power flow engine in Rust. The engine computes solutions to power flow (PF) problems (DC/AC), optimal power flow (OPF) problems (DC/SOCWR/AC), and sensitivities of those solutions with respect to problem parameters.

With tellegen, you can differentiate locational marginal prices, voltage magnitudes from AC power flow, and solutions from the Jabr relaxation of AC OPF. Sensitivities are computed analytically. The package is licensed under the Apache License 2.0 or the MIT License, at your option.

The W space SOCWR formulation follows the standard Jabr second order cone (SOC) relaxation (R. A. Jabr, 2006) as implemented in PowerModels.jl (https://github.com/lanl-ansi/PowerModels.jl, BSD 3 Clause). PowerModels.jl was used as a formulation reference.

